From: Tony Liu <Bo.Liu@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 18 May 2010 10:44:57 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] lsi_app3k: extend IO region

There is a total of 512M DDR DRAM on-board, the original
IO_ADDRESS limition causes the loss of 128M DDR DRAM, adjust it to
make all on-board DRAM available.

Signed-off-by: Tony Liu <Bo.Liu@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-app/include/mach/io.h |    4 ++--
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-app/include/mach/io.h b/arch/arm/mach-app/include/mach/io.h
index cdfeb42..f605581 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-app/include/mach/io.h
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-app/include/mach/io.h
@@ -22,8 +22,8 @@
 #define __ASM_ARCH_IO_H
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_ARCH_APP3K
-#define IO_ADDRESS     0xe0000000
-#define IO_SPACE_LIMIT 0x10000000
+#define IO_ADDRESS     0xe8000000
+#define IO_SPACE_LIMIT 0xffffffff
 #endif
 
 #define __io(a)			(a)
